label.value: abolished nuclear MIS12/MIND complex binding

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which nuclear MIS12/MIND complex binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

definition.value: This term can be used for any interaction with a protein complex that is assayed in a mutant, whether or not the mutated gene product is one of the interacting proteins. We recommend noting which proteins were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased centromere clustering at nuclear periphery during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of centromeres and associated kinetochores into a cluster at the nuclear periphery is decreased during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle. Centromere-kinetochore complexes normally cluster near the old spindle pole body during mitotic interphase.

label.value: spindle pole bodies present in increased numbers during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype  observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain more spindle pole bodies (SPBs) than normal. In this phenotype, extra SPBs typically contain normal components but seldom attach to spindle microtubules.

label.value: dispersed filamentous actin

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which filamentous actin (F-actin) is present in a dispersed form in the cell. Normal F-actin structures (cables and cortical patches) may or may not also be present.

label.value: abolished DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which a DNA-directed DNA polymerase activity is absent.

label.value: normal 5'-deoxyribose-5-phosphate lyase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate and other catalytic properties of a 5'-deoxyribose-5-phosphate lyase activity are normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal galactosyltransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a galactosyltransferase activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased galactosyltransferase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of a galactosyltransferase activity is decreased.

label.value: decreased galactose level in cell surface glycoprotein glycan

value.value: A phenotype in which the glycan moiety of a glycoprotein found at the cell surface contains a lower amount of galactose residues than normal. In wild-type cells, glycoprotein glycans contain mannose and galactose residues in a 1:1.2 ratio, and the galactose residues are connected by alpha-1,2 linkages.

label.value: abnormal deadenylation-dependent decay

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the degradation of messenger RNA (mRNA) molecules via the deadenylation-dependent pathway, which includes poly(A) tail shortening, is abnormal.

label.value: decreased nuclear-transcribed mRNA poly(A) tail shortening

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which shortening of the poly(A) tail of a messenger RNA (mRNA) molecule is decreased.

label.value: decreased gross chromosomal rearrangement

value.value: A cell phenotype in which large chromosomal rearrangements occur less frequently than in wild type cells. Chromosomal rearrangements may include deletions, duplications, inversions, and translocations.

label.value: normal gross chromosomal rearrangement frequency

value.value: A cell phenotype in which large chromosomal rearrangements occur at a normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) frequency. Chromosomal rearrangements may include deletions, duplications, inversions, and translocations.

label.value: decreased protein level in RNA polymerase II core complex

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of a protein measured in the RNA polymerase II core complex is lower than normal.

definition.value: Use this term for cases where the relative abundance of one or more specific proteins in the proteasome is decreased, altering the proteasome stoichiometry. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished histone H3-K9 trimethylation at centromere inner repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which trimethylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in centromere inner repeat regions does not occur.

label.value: increased histone H3-K9 acetylation at centromere outer repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in centromere outer repeat regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: increased histone H3-K14 acetylation at centromere inner repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 14 of histone H3 in centromere inner repeat regions occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: normal histone H3-K9 acetylation at centromere inner repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 9 of histone H3 in centromere inner repeat regions is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal histone H3-K14 acetylation at centromere inner repeat during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which acetylation of lysine at position 14 of histone H3 in centromere inner repeat regions is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased protein localization to chromatin at centromere outer repeat

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to chromatin at centromere outer repeat regions is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal vegetative cell growth rate

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cells elongate at a normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) rate during the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Cell growth is the process in which a cell irreversibly increases in size over time by accretion and biosynthetic production of matter similar to that already present.

definition.value: Note that this term refers to growth at the level of any individual cell, and that it specifies only that the rate of increase in cell size due to metabolism is normal. Other aspects of the cell's biology may be abnormal, and other abnormalities may affect increase in cell number (population growth). Also see 'cell population growth phenotype' (FYPO:0000139) and its descendants.

label.value: abnormal cell growth rate

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the rate of cell growth is abnormal. Cell growth is the irreversible increase in size over time by accretion and biosynthetic production of matter similar to that already present.

definition.value: Note that this term refers to growth, i.e. increase in size, of an individual cell. If you have measured the rate or extent of growth of a culture in liquid medium or on plates, use one of the 'cell population growth' terms.

label.value: slow vegetative cell growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which cells elongate more slowly than normal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

definition.value: Note that this term refers to growth, i.e. increase in size, of an individual cell. If you have measured the rate or extent of growth of a culture in liquid medium or on plates, use one of the 'cell population growth' terms.

label.value: viable small vegetative cell with normal cell growth rate

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetatively growing cell is viable and elongates at a normal rate, but divides when a shorter time than normal has elapsed since the previous cell division. Daughter cells therefore have an abnormally low volume. Note that these small viable cells result from a cell cycle size regulation defect.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: viable small vegetative cell with slow cell growth

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype in which a vegetatively growing cell is viable, but elongates at a slower rate than normal and divides with an abnormally low volume.

definition.value: Note that if you have done an experiment that assays the viability of a population of cells, such as looking at colony growth or growth in liquid culture, you should also annotate to 'viable cell population' (FYPO:0002058) or one of its descendants.

label.value: premature protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body begins earlier than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abolished protein localization to mitotic spindle pole body during mitosis

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the mitotic spindle pole body does not occur during mitosis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: sensitive to 4-fluorophenylalanine

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to 4-fluorophenylalanine. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of 4-fluorophenylalanine that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: decreased cytosolic zinc level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of zinc ion measured in the cytosol is lower than normal.

label.value: increased cytosolic zinc level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of zinc ion measured in the cytosol is higher than normal.

label.value: normal RNA level during cellular response to zinc ion starvation

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to zinc ion starvation is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal RNA level during cellular response to replete zinc

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to replete levels of zinc ion is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: delayed onset of primary cell septum biogenesis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which primary cell septum biogenesis begins later than normal.

label.value: premature primary cell septum biogenesis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which primary cell septum biogenesis begins earlier than normal.

label.value: normal onset of primary cell septum biogenesis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which primary cell septum biogenesis  begins at the normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) time relative to other cell cycle events.

label.value: increased rate of primary cell septum biogenesis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of primary cell septum biogenesis is increased.

label.value: normal glucan endo-1,3-beta-glucanase activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of glucan endo-1,3-beta-glucanase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: sensitive to magnesium chloride

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to magnesium chloride. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of magnesium chloride that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: increased protein dephosphorylation during cytokinesis

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the dephosphorylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, occurs to a greater extent than normal during cytokinesis.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal linear element maturation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which linear element maturation is abnormal. Linear element maturation is the close association of assembled LinE complexes with chromatin during meiotic prophase to form mature linear elements.

label.value: normal protein complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the assembly of a protein complex at the cellular level is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: normal LinE complex assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which LinE complex assembly is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: increased duration of meiotic S phase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the duration of progression through S phase of the meiotic cell cycle (preceding meiosis I) is longer than normal.

label.value: normal spatial extent of CENP-A containing nucleosome assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which nucleosomes containing the histone H3 variant CenH3 (also called CENP-A; Cnp1 in S. pombe) are assembled over a normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) portion of the centromeric region of the chromosome. CENP-A-containing nucleosomes are assembled into chromatin around centromeres, encompassing the central core and centromeric inner repeat regions.

label.value: increased histone H3 localization to chromatin

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of histone H3 to chromatin is increased.

label.value: normal H2A.Z level at centromere

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of the histone variant H2A.Z found associated with chromatin in centromeric regions is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: normal histone methyltransferase activity (H3-K9 specific) activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of H3-K9 specific histone methyltransferase activity is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased total protein level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the total amount of protein measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: increased total protein level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the total amount of protein measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: decreased total RNA level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the total amount of RNA measured in a cell is lower than normal.
